These instructions will guide you through installing SimpleScreenRecorder - a screen video capture tool in Linux. 
Run the following commands in the terminal:

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:maarten-baert/simplescreenrecorder
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install simplescreenrecorder

You can now open the application in the "Applications" > "Sound & Video" > "SimpleScreenRecorder"
This software should be used when capturing videos of anything you are typing/viewing on the computer.
